OL,3,CMum of teen killed in car crash voices
OL,4,Canger over government's driving reforms
OL,6,FUnder the government's new plans,
OL,7,Fdrivers over 70 could be banned if
OL,8,Fthey fail compulsory eye tests.
OL,10,FA Department for Transport spokesman
OL,11,Fsaid: "Every death on our roads is a
OL,12,Ftragedy and our thoughts remain with
OL,13,Fthe families of everyone who has lost
OL,14,Fa loved one in this way.
OL,16,F"Whilst we are not considering
OL,17,Fgraduated driving licences, we
OL,18,Fabsolutely recognise that young people
OL,19,Fare disproportionately victims of
OL,20,Ftragic incidents on our roads.
